span.font: This is a form of stack-less and Q-less traversal. The purpose for the stack / Q is find a way to go back and process ancestors or child nodes. This ends up consuming O(N) aux space. To avoid this, morris traversal is used which finds a way to go back to the ancestors without stack / Q.

How is the in-order predecessor computed?
This can be done by taking the immediate LEFT child / subtree root and proceeding to iterate till its last RIGHT.
For eg) the LEFT child of current Node A, here is Node B. Starting with Node B, iterate till there is a RIGHT node, whose RIGHT is NULL. Here its
B -> F -> E.
E's RIGHT is NULL.
Thus E becomes the in-order predecessor of Node A.
Now a TEMP link is created between this in-order predecessor Node E and Node A.
Thereby, if we ever reach Node E, then we can reach Node A back again
